					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Jack Kelly</h4>
												<p>Jack Kelly is an award-winning author and historian. His books include <em>Band of Giants</em>, which received the DAR History Medal, and <em>God Save Benedict Arnold</em>, a Finalist for the New England Book Awards. He has published five novels, and is a New York Foundation for the Arts fellow in Nonfiction Literature. Kelly has appeared on The History Channel, National Public Radio, and C-Span. He lives in New York's Hudson Valley.</p>
